This paper discusses the OpenAIRE infrastructure for research metadata, which involves storing and processing large amounts of data in a NoSQL database (HBase) and exporting it as Linked Open Data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on data storage and processing, cs.DL and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.IR, cs.CYBER, and cs.SI.
